<exercise id="ch13mod01_sques04">
<problem id="ch13mod01_sques04p">
<para id="fs-idm159641616">The Junkbuyers Company travels from home to home, looking for opportunities to buy items that would otherwise end up with the garbage, but which the company can resell or recycle. Which will be larger, the private or the social benefits?</para></problem>
<solution id="ch13mod01_sques04s">
<para id="fs-idm36084400">When the Junkbuyers Company purchases something for resale, presumably both the buyer and the seller benefit—otherwise, they would not need to make the transaction. However, the company also reduces the amount of garbage produced, which saves money for households and/or for the city that disposes of garbage. So the social benefits are larger than the private benefits.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
